## Description
The **Extract Documents (LEA) **task allows to search and extract documents from the Legal Electronic Archiving software service.

> Note

For more information, see: [How to Connect a DP3 Application to a LEA Environment via Authorization Key](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DS/How%2Bto%2BConnect%2Ba%2BDP3%2BApplication%2Bto%2Ba%2BLEA%2BEnvironment%2Bvia%2BAuthorization%2BKey).

> Important

This feature is only available on Milan tenants.

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

### Example workflow
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

## Input
The Extract Documents (LEA) task expects an XML file in input, containing the query parameters. The following mandatory parameters must be specified:

- ***legalEntityCode***: LEA legal entity code to use for the query

- ***targetEnvironmentCode***: LEA Authorization Tag

> Note

The supported modes are document and metadata extraction and search. Distribution packages and Wayout packages are not currently supported.

For more information on specific use cases, see: [Use Case 4 - Legal Electronic Archiving](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Use%2BCase%2B4%2B-%2BLegal%2BElectronic%2BArchiving).

For example:

**Input example**

`&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?&gt;
&lt;FILE&gt;
   &lt;DOCUMENT&gt;
      &lt;TEMPLATE name="default"&gt;
         &lt;LEA legalEntityCode="TESTLEA123" targetEnvironmentCode="ACME_FATTURE"&gt;
            &lt;Request&gt;
               &lt;SearchMetadataAction&gt;
                  &lt;DocumentMetadataSearchParameters&gt;
                     &lt;DocumentCategory code="OFFSET"&gt;&lt;/DocumentCategory&gt;
                     &lt;DocumentIssueDate from="2020-09-05" to="2020-09-05"&gt;&lt;/DocumentIssueDate&gt;
                     &lt;DocumentCategoryMetadataSearchParameters&gt;
                        &lt;Metadata name="Oggetto" value="0000000011"&gt;&lt;/Metadata&gt;
                     &lt;/DocumentCategoryMetadataSearchParameters&gt;
                  &lt;/DocumentMetadataSearchParameters&gt;
               &lt;/SearchMetadataAction&gt;
            &lt;/Request&gt;
         &lt;/LEA&gt;
      &lt;/TEMPLATE&gt;
   &lt;/DOCUMENT&gt;
&lt;/FILE&gt;`## Output
The task's output is an XML file.

> Note

The supported modes are document and metadata extraction and search. 

Distribution packages and Wayout packages are not currently supported.

For more information on specific use cases, see: [Use Case 4 - Legal Electronic Archiving](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Use%2BCase%2B4%2B-%2BLegal%2BElectronic%2BArchiving).

### Error analysis
#### Kibana logs
- [https://kibana-central.doxee.com/_plugin/kibana/app/kibana](https://kibana-central.doxee.com/_plugin/kibana/app/kibana)

#### Task's output and logs
If any errors occurred during the task's execution, they will be indicated in the task's logs as well as in the task's output.

> Note

For more information on how to download the task's logs and output, see: [Doxee Platform Batch Jobs - Managing Jobs](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-jobs).

#### LEA Extractor logs
The full logs of each LEA Extractor REST run are written in the log files on the Legal Electronic Archiving JBoss server. To access the full logs it is necessary to connect to the LEA server.

For example, run the following command to search the logs based on the environment and the job's execution time:

`$ cd /PATH/TO/JBOSS/LEA/LOGS/
# for example: /opt/jboss/domain/servers/lea01-lea/log/
$ grep -B 1 -A 5 "Lea-Ext-tenant.eks-tenant01-dev" server.log | grep "18:54"	# today's log
$ zgrep -B 1 -A 5 "Lea-Ext-tenant.eks-tenant01-dev" server.log.2023-10-31.0.gz | grep "18:54"
# all logs`The output will be similar to the following:

`18:54:00,253 INFO [it.quix.docsearch.ws.DocSearchWSManager] (http-/0.0.0.0:8080-4) *** START method searchMetadataDocuments
